WEBVTT

00:08.312 --> 00:10.140
[Lisa yawning]

00:11.185 --> 00:13.665
[yawning loudly]

00:13.709 --> 00:15.015
Ah.

00:16.581 --> 00:19.323
In case you were wondering
why I'm so tired...

00:19.367 --> 00:21.325
-I wasn't.
-I was up late

00:21.369 --> 00:24.067
watching French films...
in French.

00:24.111 --> 00:28.202
And then, last night,
my dreams were in French!

00:28.245 --> 00:30.117
My dream is you keep moving.

00:32.597 --> 00:36.340
FRENCH NARRATOR: Lisa Simpson, a bright girl in a dull school.

00:36.384 --> 00:38.081
She likes the sound
a Sharpie makes

00:38.125 --> 00:39.778
when she does well on a test.

00:39.822 --> 00:42.303
[squeaking]

00:42.346 --> 00:45.654
She adores the woody sweetness
of a fresh baritone reed.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.177
Mmm.

00:47.221 --> 00:49.092
But she hates,
more than anything,

00:49.136 --> 00:51.964
finding a place
to eat at lunch.

00:52.008 --> 00:54.141
♪

00:57.405 --> 00:59.276
[gasps, groans]

01:00.625 --> 01:02.018
[sighs]

01:05.282 --> 01:07.110
What was this?

01:07.154 --> 01:09.199
You will soon see.

01:09.243 --> 01:10.722
Frankly, I am redundant.

01:17.077 --> 01:18.817
"J. Beardsley."

01:19.644 --> 01:21.559
[gasps]
Jasper!

01:21.603 --> 01:23.300
FRENCH NARRATOR:
Suddenly, in the middle

01:23.344 --> 01:26.956
of this crap school,
a mystery!

01:26.999 --> 01:29.350
Meanwhile, for the first time
in his life,

01:29.393 --> 01:31.178
Homer would be disappointed
in a kitchen.

01:31.221 --> 01:33.180
Oh, my God. Leftovers!

01:33.223 --> 01:37.836
Air, nothing,
more air, space, air,

01:37.880 --> 01:39.795
not spaghetti, not meatloaf,

01:39.838 --> 01:42.145
missing chili,
absence of mac and cheese!

01:42.189 --> 01:43.625
There must be some food here.

01:43.668 --> 01:45.279
[gasps]

01:45.322 --> 01:47.803
The devil's trees.

01:47.846 --> 01:49.544
No!

01:49.587 --> 01:51.502
-Homie, relax.
-Okay.

01:51.546 --> 01:54.331
I've decided
to be a Tubberware salesperson.

01:54.375 --> 01:56.290
Tubberware?
Isn't that the thing

01:56.333 --> 01:58.161
where you find people
to host parties

01:58.205 --> 02:00.642
where you then sell everyone
plastic food boxes?

02:00.685 --> 02:02.731
Well, you do
your Kickstarters.

02:02.774 --> 02:05.429
Hey, if people pay
to send me on my tour

02:05.473 --> 02:08.737
of rocking chairs in the
Midwest, that helps everyone.

02:08.780 --> 02:10.608
We really could use the money.

02:10.652 --> 02:12.393
They're still garnishing
your wages

02:12.436 --> 02:14.612
after that garnish war
you waged.

02:14.656 --> 02:16.527
Please, Homie.

02:16.571 --> 02:18.225
I want to open
a checking account

02:18.268 --> 02:21.010
so the family finally has one.

02:21.053 --> 02:24.318
Marge, no wife of mine
will ever have to work.

02:24.361 --> 02:26.581
Is what men used to say
for some insane reason.

02:26.624 --> 02:28.670
You have my blessing.

02:28.713 --> 02:30.802
Where's Jasper?
He's late again.

02:30.846 --> 02:33.109
Maybe we should feed the birds
without him.

02:33.153 --> 02:35.242
Don't tell me
you fed the birds without me?

02:35.285 --> 02:37.113
You were in a coma!

02:37.157 --> 02:38.810
Mein Gott,what else happened?

02:38.854 --> 02:40.421
You won't like who's president.

02:40.464 --> 02:42.292
It's not Bernie?

02:42.336 --> 02:45.991
[Amélietheme plays]

02:46.035 --> 02:48.255
FRENCH NARRATOR: Lisa returned
Jasper's childhood,

02:48.298 --> 02:51.562
and all she wanted
was her own secret giggle.

02:51.606 --> 02:54.435
[whispers]:
Jasper.

02:54.478 --> 02:55.784
[gasps, coughs]

02:55.827 --> 02:58.352
Oh, my God.

03:01.093 --> 03:03.444
What do you got there?
A bento box?

03:03.487 --> 03:05.837
Somebody's ashes?
Apple TV?

03:05.881 --> 03:08.449
Oy. One more guess,
and I'm gonna need a nap.

03:08.492 --> 03:09.841
When I was six years old,

03:09.885 --> 03:12.148
I brought my treasure box
for show-and-tell.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.368
Another kid took it,
never gave it back.

03:14.411 --> 03:16.631
[cries softly]
And now, somehow, it's here.

03:16.674 --> 03:19.068
I've been angry my whole life,
but suddenly,

03:19.111 --> 03:22.114
the world seems... magical.

03:22.158 --> 03:24.334
FRENCH NARRATOR:
For the first time ever,

03:24.378 --> 03:26.031
Lisa experienced a feeling

03:26.075 --> 03:28.512
that could only be described
as...magnifique.

03:28.556 --> 03:30.384
I don't mean to overstate this,

03:30.427 --> 03:32.299
but the sun is shining
a little bit brighter,

03:32.342 --> 03:36.259
because of me!

03:36.303 --> 03:38.435
Tubberware?
I'd love to buy some.

03:38.479 --> 03:40.307
No, you don't buy it now.

03:40.350 --> 03:43.658
You have a party, and then
I sell it to your friends.

03:43.701 --> 03:45.399
-No!
-[sighs]

03:45.442 --> 03:47.357
You have the party
at your house...

03:47.401 --> 03:48.837
Oh.

03:48.880 --> 03:51.405
Then, when your friends
fill out the order forms, we...

03:51.448 --> 03:52.710
Oh.

03:52.754 --> 03:54.843
If you host a Tubberware party,

03:54.886 --> 03:58.325
you get an exclusive gift:
a lemonade pitcher!

03:58.368 --> 04:02.764
Ma'am, if the good Lord wanted
us to store juice in plastic,

04:02.807 --> 04:06.246
he wouldn't have made
a possum's bladder watertight.

04:08.335 --> 04:09.684
JULIO:
Okay, Marge, you're like

04:09.727 --> 04:11.860
a black hole of sadness
and split ends.

04:11.903 --> 04:13.340
What is wrong with you?

04:13.383 --> 04:16.517
I haven't booked
a single Tubberware party.

04:16.560 --> 04:18.345
I don't know why
I thought I could do this.

04:18.388 --> 04:21.913
I don't have that... What's the
Jewish word for "chutzpah"?

04:21.957 --> 04:23.654
You mean you have no confidence?

04:23.698 --> 04:26.440
I don't.
I always take the bad pancake.

04:26.483 --> 04:29.660
I spend so much time putting
sunscreen on everyone else,

04:29.704 --> 04:31.532
I get sunburned.

04:31.575 --> 04:35.710
Ooh. Just like with a doormat,
the key is underneath.

04:35.753 --> 04:37.581
-Huh?
-You know what?

04:37.625 --> 04:39.583
I will throw
a Tubberware party for you.

04:39.627 --> 04:41.585
But it's gonna take me
a while to plan.

04:41.629 --> 04:43.805
-How about tonight?
-You're on!

04:43.848 --> 04:46.460
What the heck are you doing?

04:46.503 --> 04:49.593
That's a punchbowl,
and that's for leftover lasagna.

04:49.637 --> 04:52.553
What?! Whoever heard
of leftoverlasagna?

04:52.596 --> 04:54.598
[groans] Maybe you should
just go to Moe's.

04:54.642 --> 04:57.166
Fine, but I'm not
gonna get drunk.

04:57.209 --> 05:00.474
Oh, okay, sweetie,
I'll get drunk.

05:00.517 --> 05:02.693
I just can't stay sober at you.

05:02.737 --> 05:04.478
[groans] Aah!

05:04.521 --> 05:06.784
I can't do this.
I can't do this!

05:06.828 --> 05:09.700
Can't? Can't?
Marge, I never want

05:09.744 --> 05:13.356
to hear you use
the C-A-next-Tuesday word again.

05:13.400 --> 05:16.925
You need to tap
into your female warrior side.

05:16.968 --> 05:18.492
I don't have one of those.

05:18.535 --> 05:20.494
Then we're gonna have
to create one!

05:20.537 --> 05:22.496
Makeover time!

05:22.539 --> 05:23.845
[air compressor whirring]

05:23.888 --> 05:27.544
Okay, think pretty thoughts!

05:27.588 --> 05:29.329
[hissing]

05:32.070 --> 05:35.247
Now, get rid of those things
on your feet and put these on.

05:36.466 --> 05:40.427
Mmm. It changes my whole body.

05:40.470 --> 05:44.300
[gasps]
And what is going on back there?

05:44.344 --> 05:48.304
Behold, your rump has become...
a booty, baby!

05:48.348 --> 05:49.653
Mm-hmm.

05:49.697 --> 05:53.265
Now go out there
and sell some thingies!

05:53.309 --> 05:55.267
Mmm.

05:55.311 --> 05:57.226
GRADY:
Julio,

05:57.269 --> 05:58.619
what is this?
I don't want to sit

05:58.662 --> 06:00.403
through some kind
of sales pitch.

06:00.447 --> 06:03.014
I just want a simple evening
of appetizers,

06:03.058 --> 06:05.626
cocktails and nitrous oxide.

06:05.669 --> 06:07.802
[lower voice]:
Hello, boys.

06:07.845 --> 06:09.978
I see you're checking out
the merchandise.

06:10.021 --> 06:13.808
Let me assure you,
the lids match the tubs.

06:13.851 --> 06:15.026
[all laughing]

06:15.070 --> 06:18.682
Mm. Mm-hmm.

06:18.726 --> 06:22.207
Oh. You should have told us this
was a drag Tubberware party.

06:22.251 --> 06:25.515
He's the most convincing woman
I've ever seen.

06:25.559 --> 06:27.038
Oh, oh, yes, yes.

06:27.082 --> 06:29.214
Heis quite the impersonator.

06:29.258 --> 06:31.478
He calls himself "Marge."

06:31.521 --> 06:33.828
Perfect! "Marge."

06:33.871 --> 06:36.918
If she were any more camp,
she'd be a Coleman lantern.

06:36.961 --> 06:41.009
All right, boys,
let's put tops on bottoms.

06:41.052 --> 06:44.578
[all laughing]

06:44.621 --> 06:46.841
And you wanted to go dancing.

06:46.884 --> 06:49.234
Mm. Mm-mm-mm-mm.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.280
And voilà-- a Marge-tini!

06:51.323 --> 06:52.934
But don't worry.

06:52.977 --> 06:55.937
That's not the only surprise
I've got tucked away.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.243
-She's funny.
-Bea Arthur funny?

06:58.287 --> 07:00.115
No one's that funny.

07:00.158 --> 07:02.944
FRENCH NARRATOR: And that night,
Marge sold more Tubberware

07:02.987 --> 07:04.467
than she ever imagined.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.470
And I,
drawn by the farcical premise,

07:07.514 --> 07:09.646
began narrating her story, too.

07:09.690 --> 07:11.387
Look at all these orders!

07:11.431 --> 07:12.910
I'm really good at this.

07:12.954 --> 07:15.522
Yeah, well, uh, you see, um...

07:15.565 --> 07:17.524
"Marge" is good at this.

07:17.567 --> 07:20.048
Yeah, Marge. Me. I'm Marge.

07:20.091 --> 07:21.745
Okay, so here's
what happened, okay?

07:21.789 --> 07:24.835
This is so important,
I'm gonna drop the accent.

07:24.879 --> 07:26.620
[without accent]:
Everyone thought

07:26.663 --> 07:28.448
-you were a drag queen.
-[gasps]

07:31.799 --> 07:33.714
I felt so pretty,
but the whole time,

07:33.757 --> 07:35.672
people thought I was a man.

07:35.716 --> 07:38.501
A man who looked like
a fabulous woman!

07:38.545 --> 07:42.723
Drag queens can be
very beautiful. Exhibit: me.

07:42.766 --> 07:45.334
I call myself
"Penelope Cruising."

07:45.377 --> 07:48.729
I was Mr. Burns's date
for the Kennedy Center Honors.

07:48.772 --> 07:50.644
See? Look how cute I am.

07:50.687 --> 07:53.995
All his dates have
to give him transfusions.

07:54.038 --> 07:57.607
Now I know why he said
I was his type.

07:57.651 --> 07:59.087
You get it?

07:59.130 --> 08:01.524
Well, the next time,
I'm just going to be myself.

08:01.568 --> 08:04.527
But that wasyou,
you with confidence.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.529
Oh, you're just being nice.

08:06.573 --> 08:08.792
It was ju! It was ju! It was ju!

08:08.836 --> 08:11.578
And besides,
the top Tubberware sellers--

08:11.621 --> 08:13.231
they're all drag queens.

08:13.275 --> 08:15.277
What? That can't be true.

08:20.761 --> 08:22.589
So, what do you say, Marge?
Are you in it to win it?

08:22.632 --> 08:24.591
CONTAINER:
Go for it, Marge!

08:24.634 --> 08:27.202
Who cares if what's outside
doesn't match what's inside?

08:27.245 --> 08:31.772
I'm labeled "Lunch Snacks,"
but people use me to store pot.

08:31.815 --> 08:33.817
And I'm for storing bread.

08:33.861 --> 08:37.821
All the bread you're gonna make
selling Tubberware.

08:37.865 --> 08:39.736
Did you just high-five
that bowl?

08:39.780 --> 08:42.565
Be cool, Marge. Be cool.

08:42.609 --> 08:46.264
Homer, order anything you like.
It's on me.

08:46.308 --> 08:48.179
Anything.

08:48.223 --> 08:50.704
Okay. I'm gonna need two menus
and four tables.

08:50.747 --> 08:52.444
And get rid
of all this silverware.

08:52.488 --> 08:54.708
-It just slows me down.
-I got it. I got it.

08:54.751 --> 08:58.363
We need help. Someone get Mama
back from bingo.

08:58.407 --> 09:00.365
I am on my way.

09:00.409 --> 09:02.063
But all you need is a "G."

09:02.106 --> 09:05.066
You should be like the "G"
in gnocchi--

09:05.109 --> 09:07.590
silent!

09:07.634 --> 09:10.680
Mmm. Oh, Marge, thank you.

09:10.724 --> 09:13.378
Thank you. I'm so happy!

09:13.422 --> 09:15.467
And there it is.

09:16.817 --> 09:20.211
Leftover lasagna.

09:27.828 --> 09:29.830
D'oh!

09:29.873 --> 09:32.049
FRENCH NARRATOR: Lisa still
felt sort ofmagnifique,

09:32.093 --> 09:34.835
but the magical feeling from
her good deed started to fade.

09:34.878 --> 09:36.837
So she thought:

09:36.880 --> 09:38.882
why not secretly bring magic
into others' lives?

09:38.926 --> 09:40.667
Yes.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.843
FRENCH NARRATOR: Her first
project: restore the lost love

09:42.886 --> 09:46.281
between the identical-looking
Kirk and Luann.

09:46.324 --> 09:49.458
[Amélietheme plays]

10:00.687 --> 10:03.080
KIRK: Looks like dying my nose hair's

10:03.124 --> 10:05.909
really paying off!

10:05.953 --> 10:07.737
FRENCH NARRATOR:
Next, Lisa helped Gil,

10:07.781 --> 10:10.000
Springfield's Pepé Le Pew,
minus the charm.

10:10.044 --> 10:13.787
Sir, would ya like one?
No, huh? Well, I guess not.

10:13.830 --> 10:15.919
Ma'am? Uh, maybe next time.

10:15.963 --> 10:18.008
Come on! I only get paid
if they're all gone.

10:18.052 --> 10:20.881
And they check the trash,
believe me.

10:20.924 --> 10:23.623
Oh, my God.
People are taking them!

10:25.102 --> 10:28.584
I'm turning the heat on
in my car tonight.

10:32.414 --> 10:33.807
LISA:
Bart. Wake up.

10:33.850 --> 10:35.722
Bart! I need your help again.

10:35.765 --> 10:37.941
FRENCH NARRATOR:
But Lisa's greatest challenge

10:37.985 --> 10:39.943
was to make Mrs. Skinner
believe in her son again.

10:39.987 --> 10:42.380
So Lisa created an imaginary
journal for Seymour,

10:42.424 --> 10:44.382
one that would mend all fences.

10:44.426 --> 10:47.734
I have to get this fake diary
into Skinner's house.

10:47.777 --> 10:49.257
Here's the key.

10:49.300 --> 10:51.259
Here's a floor plan
of the house.

10:51.302 --> 10:54.262
Oh, and here's some tuna.
I'm making his cat really fat.

10:54.305 --> 10:56.699
[yawning]

10:58.396 --> 10:59.833
So Lisa hid the diary

10:59.876 --> 11:01.878
where she knew Mrs. Skinner
would find it--

11:01.922 --> 11:04.794
anywhere a grown man
would expect privacy.

11:04.838 --> 11:05.969
Huh?

11:06.013 --> 11:08.537
"Mother is a great woman."

11:08.580 --> 11:10.539
[gasps]
Seymour loves me!

11:10.582 --> 11:12.846
Oh, my God!
How does a mother apologize

11:12.889 --> 11:16.501
for 50 years
of ridiculing her son?

11:16.545 --> 11:20.201
A gift card now,
and an apology on my deathbed.

11:20.244 --> 11:23.770
Meanwhile, to help perfect
her art and increase business,

11:23.813 --> 11:25.206
Julio took Marge

11:25.249 --> 11:27.208
to Springfield's
hottest drag club,

11:27.251 --> 11:30.428
with its most confusing
bathroom signage.

11:30.472 --> 11:33.214
Marge, this is Queen Chanté,

11:33.257 --> 11:35.433
Barbra Streisman,

11:35.477 --> 11:37.566
the Mysterious Waylon,

11:37.609 --> 11:39.437
and Fiona Adams Apple.

11:39.481 --> 11:42.005
Hello, squirrel-friend.

11:42.049 --> 11:43.441
You're the tallest thing
I ever...

11:43.485 --> 11:45.226
[gasps]
And you're still getting up.

11:45.269 --> 11:47.141
Honey, I spend half my day
getting up

11:47.184 --> 11:49.012
and the other half getting down.

11:49.056 --> 11:51.188
-Oh-kurr?!
-This is the kind of confidence

11:51.232 --> 11:52.581
that you need.

11:52.624 --> 11:54.235
The secret is to imagine

11:54.278 --> 11:57.891
the fiercest version
of yourself, then realize...

11:57.934 --> 11:59.762
you arethat version!

11:59.806 --> 12:01.590
Mel, is that you?

12:01.633 --> 12:05.420
Yes! I've taped my bone
between my legs.

12:05.463 --> 12:08.162
Your Majesty,
can Marge lip-synch with us?

12:08.205 --> 12:10.817
Honey, I'll tell you
what I told Eddie Murphy:

12:10.860 --> 12:12.819
"Sure, why not?"

12:12.862 --> 12:15.038
So, tell me about
this "Marge" character.

12:15.082 --> 12:16.997
What is she like?

12:17.040 --> 12:19.173
Well, she's long-suffering,

12:19.216 --> 12:20.957
kind of a single mom...

12:21.001 --> 12:22.916
and that's it.

12:22.959 --> 12:26.963
She's a damn hero, is what
she is, sis. [clucks tongue]

12:27.007 --> 12:30.010
♪

12:31.446 --> 12:34.057
♪ You've got all eyes on you♪

12:34.101 --> 12:35.798
♪ A nasty housewife lady♪

12:35.842 --> 12:37.669
♪ Come out of your mom shell♪

12:37.713 --> 12:39.846
♪ And become a bombshell♪

12:39.889 --> 12:41.848
♪ You've got this, Margie♪

12:41.891 --> 12:43.850
♪ You're stronger
than you know♪

12:43.893 --> 12:45.677
♪ Get up and dance♪

12:45.721 --> 12:47.636
-Oh!
-♪ Get up, get up and♪

12:47.679 --> 12:49.507
♪ Sashay with Chanté♪

12:49.551 --> 12:51.074
♪ Work that blue bouffanté♪

12:51.118 --> 12:52.510
♪ Do it, do it♪

12:52.554 --> 12:53.729
♪ Oh♪

12:53.773 --> 12:55.513
♪ All the boys say♪

12:55.557 --> 12:57.298
Women can have it all.

12:57.341 --> 12:59.213
Even penises!

12:59.256 --> 13:00.649
♪ She's so chic♪

13:00.692 --> 13:02.651
♪ Such savoir faire♪

13:02.694 --> 13:04.479
♪ Serving housewife realness♪

13:04.522 --> 13:06.524
♪ Selling Tubberware♪

13:06.568 --> 13:08.744
♪ She's a female phenomenon♪

13:08.788 --> 13:11.094
♪ And much more than a mom♪

13:11.138 --> 13:12.443
♪ So sexy, so snuggable♪

13:12.487 --> 13:14.750
♪ Her cocoa is so chuggable♪

13:14.794 --> 13:16.839
♪ Our blue duck
has become a swan♪

13:16.883 --> 13:18.841
♪ She's a Glamazon.♪

13:19.929 --> 13:22.105
♪ Sashay with Chanté♪

13:22.149 --> 13:24.107
♪ Work that blue bouffanté...♪

13:24.151 --> 13:25.456
Oh, hi, Helen.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.110
Hi, Marge.

13:27.154 --> 13:28.895
I heard you're selling
Tubberware.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.897
Money troubles at home?

13:30.940 --> 13:33.116
Why are you so bitter, Helen?

13:33.160 --> 13:36.728
Is it because your husband would
rather play with his toy train

13:36.772 --> 13:38.687
than with you?

13:38.730 --> 13:39.862
-[gasps]
-All aboard!

13:39.906 --> 13:41.777
Not Helen!

13:43.126 --> 13:44.693
You better beware, Bart.

13:44.736 --> 13:46.869
Mom just grew a backbone.

13:51.047 --> 13:53.049
-[Mrs. Skinner laughs]
-You mean it, Mother?

13:53.093 --> 13:55.269
You'll finally let me take
karate lessons?

13:55.312 --> 13:57.097
I'll even buy you a gi.

13:57.140 --> 13:59.099
Oh, I won't have
to wear pajamas?

13:59.142 --> 14:01.536
Only at bedtime--
which I'm moving to

14:01.579 --> 14:03.886
after The Big Bang Theory.

14:03.930 --> 14:05.670
Bazinga!

14:05.714 --> 14:07.368
FRENCH NARRATOR:
All seemed well,

14:07.411 --> 14:09.979
but likeYoung Sheldon,
it would not last forever.

14:13.200 --> 14:16.159
Oh, hello, Mother. Karate
is so much better than I ever...

14:16.203 --> 14:18.727
Seymour! I knew
this journal was a lie!

14:18.770 --> 14:21.164
Um, how would you know that?

14:21.208 --> 14:22.992
Seymour never uses semicolons.

14:24.124 --> 14:26.126
He says they make him queasy.

14:26.169 --> 14:29.042
I don't even keep a journal.
I have no inner thoughts.

14:29.085 --> 14:31.348
I planted that journal.
I'm sorry.

14:31.392 --> 14:34.612
I did it so you'd
be nicer to your son.

14:34.656 --> 14:37.311
Nicer?! I spoiled
the little loser!

14:37.354 --> 14:39.966
But not anymore.

14:40.009 --> 14:41.532
I'm so sorry.

14:41.576 --> 14:43.143
[sobbing]

14:44.448 --> 14:46.624
Oh, my God, that poor girl.

14:46.668 --> 14:49.410
Go to her, Seymour.
Give her an "A."

14:49.453 --> 14:52.195
The teachers' union forbids me
from giving out

14:52.239 --> 14:54.371
anything more encouraging
than a pumpkin sticker.

14:54.415 --> 14:57.157
You're a disgrace
to that yellow belt!

14:57.200 --> 14:59.768
[giggling]
Look at me, boys!

14:59.811 --> 15:02.336
I'm living off my wife
like Mr. Meryl Streep!

15:02.379 --> 15:03.859
Don Gummer.

15:03.903 --> 15:06.383
Homer, do you know exactly
what Marge is up to?

15:06.427 --> 15:09.430
Because, uh, we know, and
we've told everybody except you.

15:09.473 --> 15:10.866
Like true friends.

15:10.910 --> 15:11.998
[both chuckle]

15:12.041 --> 15:13.129
What's going on?

15:13.173 --> 15:15.218
If you want to know the truth,

15:15.262 --> 15:18.004
-go to this address.
-That's the address of this bar.

15:18.047 --> 15:20.223
That's right.
Get really drunk,

15:20.267 --> 15:23.400
then go to thisaddress. Uh-huh.

15:23.444 --> 15:25.620
[groans nervously]

15:28.275 --> 15:30.233
Hello. Are you on the list?

15:30.277 --> 15:32.801
I have to be on the list
for a Tubberware party?

15:32.844 --> 15:34.629
Well, you do for thisone.

15:34.672 --> 15:38.241
Marge is like if Donna Reed
and Donna Summer combined

15:38.285 --> 15:40.896
to solve all your
food storage problems.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.159
And rumor has it, out of drag,

15:43.203 --> 15:46.641
Marge is hot, hunky and all man.

15:46.684 --> 15:48.643
My wife is none of those things!

15:48.686 --> 15:50.471
She leaves the room to burp!

15:50.514 --> 15:53.822
Marge! You didn't tell me
you're tricking all these people

15:53.865 --> 15:56.259
into thinking you're
a drag queen, when you're really

15:56.303 --> 15:59.915
a regular housewife in need
of empowerment, and now...

15:59.959 --> 16:03.049
that I say it out loud,
it doesn't seem so bad.

16:03.092 --> 16:04.702
She's not a female impersonator.

16:04.746 --> 16:07.488
-She's just a personator.
-Women co-opt everything.

16:07.531 --> 16:08.837
GEOFFREY:
Good to see

16:08.880 --> 16:10.882
another couple in trouble.

16:10.926 --> 16:12.928
-Let's go, Dewey.
-I'm not leaving

16:12.972 --> 16:15.278
till I find my butter tub.

16:15.322 --> 16:17.019
Look in the mirror.

16:20.631 --> 16:21.719
HOMER:
Kids,

16:21.763 --> 16:23.721
please give us a moment.

16:23.765 --> 16:25.506
You're cool.

16:25.549 --> 16:27.421
"Marjorie,
I'm not a perfect man,

16:27.464 --> 16:29.466
"but I like to think
I've evolved.

16:29.510 --> 16:31.033
"I've accepted
the several different actors

16:31.077 --> 16:32.643
"who played Batman.

16:32.687 --> 16:35.298
I now believe cats
should earn as much as dogs."

16:35.342 --> 16:37.213
I don't want to hear
your stupid speech.

16:37.257 --> 16:42.044
I had a moment of confidence,
and now it's destroyed.

16:42.088 --> 16:44.090
I'mgoing out.
Youcan watch the kids

16:44.133 --> 16:45.700
and wonder where Iam.

16:47.310 --> 16:49.051
[gasps]

16:49.095 --> 16:52.098
[fake snoring]

16:52.141 --> 16:55.579
No. I don't want anything
to do with him.

16:57.538 --> 17:00.280
[Lisa crying]

17:00.323 --> 17:03.283
Lisa, are you okay?

17:03.326 --> 17:05.676
I tried to play God,
and like the real God,

17:05.720 --> 17:07.417
it went horribly wrong.

17:07.461 --> 17:10.333
FRENCH NARRATOR: Life was a struggle for the Simpson women.

17:10.377 --> 17:11.552
Even Maggie.

17:11.595 --> 17:14.511
But where there is life,
there is hope.

17:15.773 --> 17:17.732
[sound of rooster crowing]

17:17.775 --> 17:20.778
That was the beginning
of a new day, a wonderful day,

17:20.822 --> 17:23.694
a day that would soon change
the Simpson women forever.

17:23.738 --> 17:26.741
[Amélietheme plays]

17:33.139 --> 17:34.966
♪

17:36.403 --> 17:38.144
[sighs]:
Oh...

17:40.015 --> 17:42.235
Read the tots.

17:42.278 --> 17:43.975
LISA:
"Go to the roof"?

17:44.019 --> 17:45.151
Enjoy.

17:45.194 --> 17:47.370
Next!

17:47.414 --> 17:48.502
NELSON:
Huh?

17:48.545 --> 17:50.373
Aw, man!

17:53.028 --> 17:55.335
Lisa, would you
join us for lunch?

17:55.378 --> 17:59.339
We decided to bring some magic
into yourlife.

18:02.516 --> 18:05.040
Ah, you deserve it, sweetie.
You're the only person

18:05.084 --> 18:07.825
in this town who thinks about
someone other than herself.

18:07.869 --> 18:11.394
The only person who would listen
to old Gil when he...

18:11.438 --> 18:14.397
She had finally found
her place to eat lunch.

18:14.441 --> 18:17.183
But what is this? Has Homer
lost his will to drink?

18:17.226 --> 18:19.185
Homer, we're sorry we razzed ya.

18:19.228 --> 18:21.274
We were just trying
to hurt your feelings.

18:21.317 --> 18:22.971
I am so sorry.

18:23.014 --> 18:24.842
I don't know what I can do.

18:24.886 --> 18:26.844
Nothing you cando.
Change your name,

18:26.888 --> 18:29.369
glue on a wig
and find yourself a new woman.

18:29.412 --> 18:30.848
[gasps]
That's it!

18:30.892 --> 18:32.546
Moe, you're a genius!

18:32.589 --> 18:34.156
Wish me luck.

18:36.680 --> 18:39.814
Why do people always stride out
without paying their tab?

18:39.857 --> 18:42.860
I have no idea.
But as God is my witness,

18:42.904 --> 18:45.254
I will find out!

18:47.822 --> 18:50.433
You two stay right there.

18:50.477 --> 18:51.608
♪

18:51.652 --> 18:54.394
Everyone, I have
two enormously sad things

18:54.437 --> 18:57.223
I feel a need
to tell all of you.

18:57.266 --> 18:59.399
Number one--
I've deceived you.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.662
I'm not a drag queen.

19:01.705 --> 19:03.794
[chuckles]
Girl, you didn't deceive nobody.

19:03.838 --> 19:05.405
We all knew.

19:05.448 --> 19:07.798
I didn't know,
but I'm super self-involved.

19:07.842 --> 19:10.018
Oh. Now number two.

19:10.061 --> 19:12.020
FRENCH NARRATOR: And, as always
happens in such matters,

19:12.063 --> 19:14.022
number two is the kicker.

19:14.065 --> 19:15.458
My husband and I have had

19:15.502 --> 19:17.591
more than the usual number
of scrapes,

19:17.634 --> 19:20.376
but we've always
gotten back to our love.

19:20.420 --> 19:21.899
But this time,

19:21.943 --> 19:25.251
you all made me feel
understood and supported,

19:25.294 --> 19:29.864
and therefore made me realize
how selfish Homer is.

19:29.907 --> 19:32.258
-ALL: Oh...
-Oh, honey.

19:32.301 --> 19:34.825
And what hurts the most
is that I can't imagine

19:34.869 --> 19:38.612
there's anything he can say
or do to make me come back.

19:38.655 --> 19:40.657
HOMER:
Oh. Well, then I went through

19:40.701 --> 19:42.703
a lot of work for nothing.

19:42.746 --> 19:45.706
-Homie.
-Honey, I understand it now.

19:45.749 --> 19:48.404
The feeling of power,
the mystery,

19:48.448 --> 19:51.407
wondering:
is she or isn't she?

19:51.451 --> 19:54.062
Hey, believe me,
nobody is wondering, baby.

19:54.105 --> 19:56.107
♪

19:57.544 --> 19:58.936
Ow!

19:58.980 --> 20:00.895
If you don't go to him,
Marge, I will.

20:00.938 --> 20:02.940
And he will never leave
my kitchen.

20:02.984 --> 20:07.380
My pulled pork banh mi
keeps baby in the cradle.

20:07.423 --> 20:09.469
Oh, Homie, I love you!

20:09.512 --> 20:12.646
["You Make Me Feel"
by Sylvester playing]

20:12.689 --> 20:14.909
♪ When we're
out there dancing...♪

20:14.952 --> 20:18.086
Having a man dressed
like a woman

20:18.129 --> 20:20.654
to win back his woman
who pretended to be

20:20.697 --> 20:22.482
a man dressed like a woman

20:22.525 --> 20:25.485
is the most romantic thing
I've ever seen.

20:25.528 --> 20:27.313
FRENCH NARRATOR:
And so all was well.

20:27.356 --> 20:30.664
Au revoir
jusqu'à la prochaine fois,

20:30.707 --> 20:31.926
or, in English...

20:31.969 --> 20:34.363
Bye!

20:38.585 --> 20:40.761
So, are you a...
you're a drag queen now?

20:40.804 --> 20:43.285
I don't know. I guess these days
it's okay for everyone

20:43.329 --> 20:46.723
-to be everything.
-So, miss, are you alone?

20:46.767 --> 20:48.464
It's me, Homer!

20:48.508 --> 20:50.553
Hmm? Oh!

20:50.597 --> 20:54.253
All the good ones
are either married or Homer.

21:39.385 --> 21:41.300
Shh!

